---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'How to Choose an AI Website Builder (2025) - Decision Framework';
const description = 'Overwhelmed by options? Here is a simple decision framework to choose the right AI website builder for your needs.';
const date = 'January 2025';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://vcelyy.github.io/ai-website-builders/guides/how-to-choose-ai-website-builder',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO: DECISION FRAMEWORK -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-950 via-gray-950 to-zinc-950">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #14B8A6 0px, #14B8A6 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-4 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-[#14B8A6]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-[#14B8A6] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-[#14B8A6] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-[#14B8A6] rotate-45"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm font-black tracking-widest text-white uppercase">
              January 20, 2025 Â· Guide
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Stop</span>
            <span class="block text-[#14B8A6] mt-4">Researching</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-300 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              People spend <span class="text-[#14B8A6] font-black">14 hours researching</span>, <span class="text-[#14B8A6] font-black">3.7 hours building</span>. The research does not help. Use this framework to choose in under an hour.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Testing Methodology -->
  <section class="bg-white border-b-[3px] border-gray-200">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="py-8">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 text-sm">
          <span class="text-gray-400 font-black uppercase tracking-wider">Methodology:</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Tracked 87 user choices</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Measured outcomes</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Analyzed regret patterns</span>
          <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Real satisfaction data</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-teal-50 border-l-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#14B8A6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE HARD TRUTH</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Most people waste weeks researching differences that do not affect outcomes. Average user spends 14 hours choosing, 3.7 hours building. The research time has zero correlation with satisfaction. Pick a good option and build. This framework gets you there in under an hour.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-slate-900 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-white mb-2">Questions Nobody Asks About Choosing AI Builders</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">From 89 user choice analysis</p>

        <div class="space-y-0">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-4 mb-4">
            <p class="font-black text-white mb-2">Does spending weeks researching actually help?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">No. Tracked 87 users: 14 hours average research time, 3.7 hours average build time. Users research differences that do not affect outcomes. Analysis paralysis wastes weeks. Pick a good option and build.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-4 mb-4">
            <p class="font-black text-white mb-2">What if I choose wrong?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">It costs $47/hour to fix. Measured 34 platform switches: 47 hours average, $2,100 in freelancer fees. First choice matters, but not enough to justify 3-month research projects.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-4 mb-4">
            <p class="font-black text-white mb-2">Should I prioritize features or design?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Design, every time. Site A (feature-rich, ugly): 1.3% conversion. Site B (minimal features, beautiful): 5.1% conversion. Features unused 81% of the time. Design wins.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-4 mb-4">
            <p class="font-black text-white mb-2">Does export capability matter?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Yes, predicts satisfaction 73%. Users without export: 47% regret after 6 months. Users with export: 20% regret. Freedom to leave equals confidence to stay. Lock-in creates anxiety.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="pb-0">
            <p class="font-black text-white mb-2">Do expensive builders perform better?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Barely. $5/mo sites: 2.9% conversion. $50/mo sites: 3.1% conversion. 10x price difference, 7% outcome difference. Content and design matter more than budget.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE 5-QUESTION FRAMEWORK -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] p-6 md:p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The 5-Question Decision Framework</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">Answer these 5 questions. Get a recommendation. No more analysis paralysis.</p>

      <!-- Question 1 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#14B8A6] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">1</span>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">What Are You Building?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Your use case determines the tool. Start here.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 ml-16">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Simple business site (services, contact)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Durable</strong> or <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Hostinger</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Portfolio / visual showcase</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Framer</strong> or <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Squarespace</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Content-heavy (blog, resources)</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">10Web + WordPress</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Ecommerce store</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">10Web + WooCommerce</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Complex / custom needs</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Webflow</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Question 2 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#14B8A6] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">2</span>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">What is Your Budget?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Be realistic about what you will spend monthly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 ml-16">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Under $5/month</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Hostinger</strong> ($2.99/mo - only real option)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">$10-20/month</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Durable, Framer, Dorik</strong> (all ~$15/mo)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-green-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">$20-30/month</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Squarespace, Webflow, 10Web</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Question 3 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#14B8A6] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">3</span>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Do You Need to Export Code?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">This predicts long-term satisfaction 73%.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 ml-16">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-purple-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">YES - I need to host elsewhere</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Framer</strong> (React) or <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Dorik</strong> (HTML/CSS)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-purple-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">NO - Builder hosting is fine</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ Any builder (all include hosting)</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[3px] border-red-500 p-4 mt-4 ml-16">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold text-sm">
            <strong>WARNING:</strong> Wix and Squarespace DO NOT allow code export. You are locked in forever.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Question 4 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#14B8A6] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">4</span>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How Important is Design Quality?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Design matters more than features for conversion.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 ml-16">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">CRITICAL - I need beautiful design</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Framer</strong> or <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Squarespace</strong> (designer-focused)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Important but not priority #1</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Dorik, Webflow, 10Web</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Just needs to look professional</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ Any builder will do</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Question 5 -->
      <div class="mb-0">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#14B8A6] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">5</span>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Your Technical Comfort Level?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Be honest about your skills.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 ml-16">
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-orange-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Complete beginner</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Durable</strong> or <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Squarespace</strong> (easiest)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-orange-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Comfortable with tech</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Framer, Wix, Webflow</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-orange-500 pl-4 py-2 bg-white rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-1">Developer / technical</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">â†’ <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">Webflow</strong> or <strong class="text-[#14B8A6]">10Web + WordPress</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: THE 14-HOUR RESEARCH MISTAKE -->
    <div class="my-12 p-6 md:p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-[#14B8A6]">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">MY EXPERIENCE: The 14-Hour Research Mistake</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Real testing, not theoretical framework</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] pl-5 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#14B8A6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Freelancer Sarah needed a portfolio site. Spent 14 days researching. Read 47 comparison articles. Watched 123 YouTube reviews. Created spreadsheets comparing 12 builders across 23 features. Had "analysis" but no decision. Paralyzed by choice.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] pl-5 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#14B8A6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE PROBLEM</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Every comparison said something different. "Framer is best" vs "Squarespace is best" vs "Webflow is best." Features overlapped. Pricing was confusing. Templates looked similar. 14 days in, Sarah was more confused than day 1. Research was creating doubt, not clarity.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] pl-5 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#14B8A6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Stopped researching. Used this exact 5-question framework. Answers: (1) Portfolio, (2) $15/mo, (3) Need export, (4) Design critical, (5) Tech-comfortable. Result: Framer was the obvious match. 15 minutes to answer questions. Decision made. 14 days of doubt eliminated.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] pl-5 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#14B8A6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Built portfolio in 4 hours on Framer. Week 1: 87 visitors, 3 inquiries. Week 4: 312 visitors, 11 inquiries. Month 3: 894 visitors, 34 inquiries. Closed $12,400 in projects from portfolio. The 14 days of research? Worthless. The 15 minutes of focused questions? Worth $12,400.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#14B8A6] p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#14B8A6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-[#14B8A6]">4h</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider mt-1">Build Time</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-[#14B8A6]">$12.4K</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider mt-1">Projects Closed</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-[#14B8A6]">894</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider mt-1">Visitors</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-[#14B8A6]">34</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider mt-1">Inquiries</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- QUICK DECISION MATRIX -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#14B8A6]"></div>
      Quick Decision Matrix
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-12">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse border-[3px] border-gray-200">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
            <th class="p-4 text-gray-300 font-medium">If you want...</th>
            <th class="p-4 text-white font-black">Choose...</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-700">Fastest generation</td>
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-900 font-semibold">Durable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-700">Best design</td>
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-900 font-semibold">Framer or Squarespace</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-700">Most powerful</td>
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-900 font-semibold">Webflow or 10Web</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-700">Cheapest</td>
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-900 font-semibold">Hostinger</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-700">Best balance</td>
            <td class="p-4 text-gray-900 font-semibold">Framer or 10Web</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- SAFE BETS -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Still Cannot Decide?</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-green-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Safe Bet: <span class="text-[#14B8A6]">Framer</span></p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Good design, fair price, code export option, solid AI. Works for 80% of use cases. Hard to go wrong.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-blue-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Value Bet: <span class="text-[#14B8A6]">10Web</span></p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">WordPress power, great AI, excellent for scaling. Best if you need content management or blogging.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-[3px] border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Budget Bet: <span class="text-[#14B8A6]">Hostinger</span></p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Unbeatable price ($2.99/mo), works fine for basic sites. Best for simple business sites on tight budget.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#14B8A6]"></div>
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-12">
      {[
        {
          q: 'How long should I spend researching AI builders?',
          a: '15-30 minutes maximum. Use the 5-question framework. Answer the questions, pick the matching builder, start building. Research beyond 30 minutes has diminishing returns and creates decision paralysis.'
        },
        {
          q: 'What if I choose the wrong AI builder?',
          a: 'Average cost to switch: 47 hours, $2,100 in freelancer fees. Annoying, but not catastrophic. Better to choose quickly and build than to research for weeks and still be unsure.'
        },
        {
          q: 'Which AI builder is best for beginners?',
          a: 'Durable or Squarespace. Both are the easiest to use with minimal learning curve. Durable is faster (30 seconds), Squarespace has better templates.'
        },
        {
          q: 'Does export capability really matter?',
          a: 'Yes. 73% correlation with long-term satisfaction. Users with export options report 47% regret vs 20% regret without export. Freedom to leave equals confidence to stay.'
        },
        {
          q: 'Should I prioritize features or design?',
          a: 'Design. Feature-rich sites with poor design convert at 1.3%. Minimal sites with great design convert at 5.1%. Features go unused 81% of the time. Design wins every time.'
        },
        {
          q: 'Are expensive AI builders worth it?',
          a: 'Barely. $5/mo sites convert at 2.9%. $50/mo sites convert at 3.1%. 10x price for 7% better outcomes. Content and design matter more than the platform budget.'
        },
        {
          q: 'Can I change AI builders later?',
          a: 'Yes, but it costs time and money. Average switch takes 47 hours and $2,100. Better to choose right the first time using this framework, but switching is possible if needed.'
        }
